To estimate these growth trajectories, we used a three-level hierarchical linear growth model (Raudenbush & Bryk, 2002; Singer & Willett, 2002) with repeated observations of WJ III scores indexed at Level 1 by time (indexed by the number of weeks since taking the pretests), time squared (to allow for increasing or decreasing learning rates over first and second grade), time since starting MR, and time since completing MR; at Level 2 by student level demographics; and at Level 3 by school characteristics (e.g., site). To assess whether gains made in MR tutoring were maintained after the tutoring was completed, we constructed a time-varying covariate (POSTMRTIME
